{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/7728207.Svetlana_Alexievich", "name": "Svetlana Alexievich", "birth_date": "1948-05-31 00:00:00", "genres": ["Journalism", "Nonfiction"], "influences": ["Fyodor Dostoyevsky", "Ales Adamovich"], "avg_rating": 4.45, "num_reviews": 7785, "num_ratings": 51391, "about": "Svetlana Alexievich was born in Ivano-Frankivsk, Ukraine, in 1948 and has spent most of her life in the Soviet Union and present-day Belarus, with prolonged periods of exile in Western Europe. Starting out as a journalist, she developed her own distinctive nonfiction genre, which gathers a chorus of voices to describe a specific historical moment. Her works include War\u2019s Unwomanly Face (1985), Last Witnesses (1985), Zinky Boys (1990), Voices from Chernobyl (1997), and Secondhand Time (2013). She has won many international awards, including the 2015 Nobel Prize in Literature \u201cfor her polyphonic writings, a monument to suffering and courage in our time.\u201d"}
