{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/53352.Paul_Creswick", "name": "Paul Creswick", "death_date": "1947-04-13 00:00:00", "genres": ["Classics", "Science Fiction"], "avg_rating": 4.0, "num_reviews": 91, "num_ratings": 1323, "about": "James Paul Creswick (b. 1866) published his first story, \"The Only Prince\" in The Quarto in 1897. He is also known for his ghost story The Beaten Path: A Fantasy (1924) and sci-fi novel The Turning Wheel (1928), which combined mystical themes with contemporary disaster motifs. His Robin Hood and his Adventures (1902) is one of the tale's most famous adaptations."}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/70045.Suzanne_White", "name": "Suzanne White", "genres": ["Psychology", "Character Studies", "Ebooks"], "avg_rating": 3.89, "num_reviews": 73, "num_ratings": 998, "about": "SUZANNE WHITE (SEE BOOK TITLES BELOW PLEASE) Author/Astrologer Suzanne White is American, but she lives in France and Buenos Aires. She has been a college professor, a fashion model, a journalist, an interpreter, a novelist, a fireworks salesperson, director of a Parisian Couture boutique, an elevator operator, a shoe salesperson, a single mother and a simultaneous translator. White is well known as the \"High Priestess\" of both Chinese &amp; Western Astrologies. She has published many best-selling books on both western and Chinese Astrology. (see below for titles) Not only is she respected in her field, all of Suzanne White's Astrology books sell steadily and remain in print. Since 1995, White has been a continued presence on the Internet, SUZANNE WHITE (SEE BOOK TITLES BELOW PLEASE) Author/Astrologer Suzanne White is American, but she lives in France and Buenos Aires. She has been a college professor, a fashion model, a journalist, an interpreter, a novelist, a fireworks salesperson, director of a Parisian Couture boutique, an elevator operator, a shoe salesperson, a single mother and a simultaneous translator. White is well known as the \"High Priestess\" of both Chinese &amp; Western Astrologies. She has published many best-selling books on both western and Chinese Astrology. (see below for titles) Not only is she respected in her field, all of Suzanne White's Astrology books sell steadily and remain in print. Since 1995, White has been a continued presence on the Internet, at first working for both AOL and Disney sites. In 2000, she started her own web site http://www.suzannewhite.com. This most original web site has been an enormous success and given Suzanne White's name even more global recognition than she previously enjoyed. Since 2008, Whi