{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/7330.Sinclair_Lewis", "name": "Sinclair Lewis", "birth_date": "1885-02-07 00:00:00", "death_date": "1951-01-10 00:00:00", "genres": ["Fiction"], "influences": ["Jacques Loeb", "Upton Sinclair", "F\u00e9lix d'Herelle"], "avg_rating": 3.76, "num_reviews": 5730, "num_ratings": 71989, "about": "Awarded the Nobel Prize in Literature in 1930 \"for his vigorous and graphic art of description and his ability to create, with wit and humor, new types of characters.\" His works are known for their insightful and critical views of American capitalism and materialism between the wars. He is also respected for his strong characterizations of modern working women. H.L. Mencken wrote of him, \"[If] there was ever a novelist among us with an authentic call to the trade...it is this red-haired tornado from the Minnesota wilds.\""}
